Cleaning the data and more

supermarket <- supermarket %>%
  filter(PriceSEK > 0) %>%
  mutate(DiscountSEK = ifelse(is.na(DiscountSEK) | DiscountSEK < 0, 0, DiscountSEK),
         NormalPrice = PriceSEK + DiscountSEK)

  summarize(count = n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(count))

The 10 items for which there is the largest total sale.

itemsSale <- supermarket %>%
  group_by(Item) %>%
  summarize(total = sum(TotalSale)) %>%
  arrange(desc(total))

Figures

supermarket %>%
  filter(Item %in% itemsSale$Item[1:10]) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = NormalSale, y = TotalSale, color = Item)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  scale_x_log10() + scale_y_log10() + 
  geom_abline()

ggplot(supermarket, aes(x = DiscountSEK / NormalPrice, y = TotalSale / NormalSale)) + 
  geom_hex() + scale_y_log10() + 
  geom_smooth(color = "red")
